<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<!--
  on-demand-sync task 7.6: entitlements for the File Provider extension
  point (com.apple.fileprovider-nonui), same App Sandbox + App Group
  shape as ../../YadoriLinkFinderSync/Extension/Extension.entitlements
  (read that file's doc comment in full for the hard-won reasoning this
  was derived from — it is not repeated verbatim here to avoid drift
  between two copies of the same long explanation; only what's
  specific to this target is noted below).

  1. App Sandbox must be ON — PlugInKit/ExtensionKit reject unsandboxed
     extensions outright, confirmed for FinderSync this session and
     expected to hold equally for the File Provider extension point
     (both are System Extensions-adjacent app-extension mechanisms
     gated by the same OS-level discovery process).
  2. Real Apple Development (or better) signing is required to *launch*
     a sandboxed extension at all — ad-hoc signing lets the process
     spawn but it dies silently right after AppSandbox init. Automatic
     signing (project.yml: CODE_SIGN_STYLE Automatic, DEVELOPMENT_TEAM
     594UQF7QX3) is reused unchanged from YadoriLinkFinderSync's target.
  3. `com.apple.security.application-groups` = group.com.juntaki.yadorilink.shared
     is the confirmed-working mechanism for this sandboxed extension to
     reach the daemon's Unix socket (`fileprovider-core/src/ipc_client.rs`
     mirrors `core/src/ipc_client.rs`'s socket_path() resolution:
     `~/Library/Group Containers/group.com.juntaki.yadorilink.shared/shell.sock`,
     no Team ID prefix). NOT independently re-verified end-to-end for
     this specific extension point in this session (only FinderSync's
     use of the same entitlement was confirmed via a real Finder
     badge/menu render) — flagged as a residual verification gap in
     tasks.md 7.8, not assumed proven by analogy alone.

  This extension additionally needs no entitlement for the File Provider
  domain mechanism itself (NSFileProviderManager/domain registration is
  not gated by an entitlement beyond normal App Sandbox membership plus
  the NSExtensionFileProviderDocumentGroup Info.plist key — see
  Info.plist's doc comment).
-->
<dict>
	<key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
	<true/>
	<key>com.apple.security.network.client</key>
	<false/>
	<key>com.apple.security.network.server</key>
	<false/>
	<key>com.apple.security.application-groups</key>
	<array>
		<string>group.com.juntaki.yadorilink.shared</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
